When an MQBrokerException occurs, more context information should be exposed to the upper layer, such as the IP of the Broker node, to help locate the problem.

## What is the purpose of the change

#2233 enhancement

## Brief changelog
before
```java
public MQBrokerException(int responseCode, String errorMessage) {
        super(FAQUrl.attachDefaultURL("CODE: " + UtilAll.responseCode2String(responseCode) + "  DESC: "
            + errorMessage));
        this.responseCode = responseCode;
        this.errorMessage = errorMessage;
    }
```
after
```java
public MQBrokerException(int responseCode, String errorMessage, String brokerAddr) {
        super(FAQUrl.attachDefaultURL("CODE: " + UtilAll.responseCode2String(responseCode) + "  DESC: "
            + errorMessage + (brokerAddr != null ? " BROKER: " + brokerAddr : "")));
        this.responseCode = responseCode;
        this.errorMessage = errorMessage;
        this.brokerAddr = brokerAddr;
    }
```

